@eric-wieser and @kbuzzard : sorry I didn't get to this sooner, I've been a bit busy. My issue with `structure` has to do with quotients. One of the primary reasons we need two-sided ideals in this generality is to properly talk about quotients of (non-commutative and non-unital) rings by ideals.

With the `abbrev` approach, my thinking is that this would come mostly for free, but I'm concerned that using a `structure` will significantly complicate this.

Actually, this brings me to my second concern, which is not necessarily directed at this PR: how do we plan to deal with quotients anyway? Currently, we make rather involved use of the fact that we have very convenient defeqs between quotients of `AddGroup`s and quotients of `CommRing`s. We're going to have to lose this at some point (I think). Do you have any good ideas for dealing with this?

